President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Dr. Thomas M. Hoenig for the position of Vice Chairman of the Board of Directors of the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation. Dr. Hoenig served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of the Federal Reserve Bank of Kansas City from 1991 to 2011. He has also worked as an economist at the Federal Reserve Bank of Kansas City since 1973, and has served as an instructor of economics at the University of Missouri-Kansas City. Dr. Hoenig holds a B.A. in Economics and Mathematics from Benedictine College, as well as an M.A. and a Ph.D. in Economics from Iowa State University.